claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: Table listing 2023–24 U.S. influenza vaccines by trade name, presentation, age indication, µg hemagglutinin per strain per dose, route, and mercury content. Includes standard-dose egg-based IIV4, cell-culture IIV4, and high-dose IIV4 entries (e.g., Fluzone High-Dose Quadrivalent at 60 µg/0.7 mL). The table does not include any entry for Flublok or show a 45 µg/0.5 mL HA content per strain; it only shows standard 15 µg doses and a 60 µg high-dose vaccine. Therefore, it does not support the claim Note: Visible portion of the table is cut off before any recombinant vaccine (RIV4) entries; immunogenicity data are not presented
